column2:
A lady walks into a pet store...
She sees a beautiful parrot with a sign on its cage: $10 OBO
The lady asks the pet shop owner, "Why so cheap?" The owner says "This bird used to live in a brothel, so he says a lot of inappropriate things." The lady can't pass up the deal and decides to get the bird anyway.
She gets the bird home and the first thing the bird says is "Finally cleaned up this dump, and the new madam isn't bad looking." The lady finds it amusing.
Her two teen daughters get home and the bird says "New whores in the house, business will be booming tonight." The girls are shocked but laugh it off.
A few hours later the woman's husband gets home and the bird says "Hey Jim."
column3:
A woman walks into a pet store and notices a beautiful parrot in a cage with a sign that says: “$10 – or best offer.”
Curious, she asks the store owner, “Why is this parrot so cheap?”
The owner replies, “Well, the bird used to live in a very lively place, so he picked up some... colorful language.”
Intrigued and amused, the woman buys the parrot and takes him home.
As soon as she sets the parrot in his new cage, he looks around and says, “Nice place! Finally some class around here.”
The woman chuckles. Later, her two teenage daughters come home, and the parrot says, “New faces! This house just keeps getting better!”
The girls laugh at the bird’s personality.
Then, a few hours later, the woman’s husband walks in the door. The parrot looks at him and says, “Hey Jim”
column4:
A lady walks into a pet store...
She sees a beautiful parrot with a sign on its cage: $10 OBO
The lady asks the pet shop owner, "Why so cheap?" The owner says "This bird used to live in a home, so he says a lot of inappropriate things." The lady can't pass up the deal and decides to get the bird anyway.
She gets the bird home and the first thing the bird says is "Finally cleaned up this place, and the new madam isn't bad looking." The lady finds it amusing.
Her two teen daughters get home and the bird says "New chores in the house, business will be booming tonight." The girls are shocked but laugh it off.
A few hours later the woman's husband gets home and the bird says "Hey Jim."
